<div class ="paragraph">
<h2>About Us</h2>
<p> Riley Graham is a Dayton and DePaul University Grad. She is a user experience design consultant at a Chicago design firm, Fuzzy Math.  Tom Longo is a Domer working as an internal auditor at Kraft Foods.  Together we enjoy travelling, live concerts, Thai food, craft beer, and enjoying the company of our dog, Pipper.  Pipper is cute and hates squirrels. </p>
</div>

<div class ="paragraph">
<h2>How We Met</h2>
<p> Tom has had a habit of showing up uninvited to the birthday parties of his sister, Maureen.  In April 2012, Maureen (Mo) and Erin invited him to crash someone else’s birthday party – Riley’s!  Mo and Erin introduced Tom and Riley who, after several Motown dance parties, decided to get hitched. </p>
</div>


<div class ="paragraph">
<h2>Our Proposal</h2>
<p> Tom, Riley, Mo, and Erin took a trip to the <a href= "http://www.chicagobotanic.org/"> Chicago Botanical Gardens </a>  in suburban Chicago, where Riley was expecting a quick stop before an evening concert.  After searching and finding a private spot on a hill, under a tree, across a small river, Tom led Riley there and proposed.  Mo and Erin took beautiful pictures and nobody cried at all, nope, no way, no crying, it was in no way emotional. </p>
</div>

<div class ="paragraph">
<h2>Our Wedding Party</h2>
<p> We are so grateful to be surrounded by many wonderful people, particularly our families. We are fortunate to be able to see our family often. Each one of these individuals helps us every day, and we hope they understand how much their help means to us! </p>
</div>









<!-- ANDREA! -->

<div class ="left">
<img src="http://www.rileyisme.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/IMG_0058.jpg" alt="Andrea and I" width="300" height="auto"/>
<div class ="paragraph">
<h2> Andrea Graham (Sister of the bride) – Maid of Honor </h2>
<p> Andrea, who dubbed Riley with the name “Lawa,” is her one and only sibling.  Andrea and Lawa did a lot together, and being about 3 years apart they were able to attend most schools together, including the University of Dayton.  Andrea, although younger, has always been wiser (Maybe that’s because Lawa always made her do everything first, most notably take booster shots first).  Andrea and Lawa are very similar, which has caused many a hair-pull back in the day.  However, I can gladly report that the last hair pull ended somewhere around ’93.  Today the girls live 461 miles apart, but that doesn’t stop their frequent visits.  In fact, there will be many more visits this year because Andrea and Conor are engaged!  Congrats you two, we love you both.
</p>
</div>
</div>




<!-- MO! -->

<div class ="left">
<img src="http://www.rileyisme.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/IMG_4060.jpg" alt="Mo" width="300" height="auto" /></div>
<div class ="paragraph">
<h2> Maureen Longo (Sister of the groom) </h2>
<p> Tom and his sister Maureen (“Mo”, “Beefcake”, “Beef”, “Barf”, “Braf”, “Berf”, etc.) have been friends since her birth in 1985, although it wasn’t Facebook-official until 2005.  Growing up, Tom and Mo played each other’s drumsets, played on competing sports teams, and had starring roles in several Longo Family Videos. Her kindness knows no bounds. She is super nice and creative and she has a sharp eye for beautiful aesthetics. We love her!
</p>
</div>









